Needs docs updates, and a longer commit message
do you want to call this? This try to forward the request to peer bmc if it is there.

setUpRedfishRoute should be called on all redfish routes.  It's for more than just aggregation.

The code here is correct.
May not be relevant for this commit. Still a question on above. If setUpRedfishRoute is mandatory for all, then why don't we call it from bmcweb framework before calling the route handlers?

because not all routes are redfish tree routes.  bmcweb supports a lot more than just redfish.

At one point Nan proposed creating a REDFISH_ROUTE handler that would do this call automatically, but it used macros where are technically against the coding standard.  I would still support if someone wanted to do that.
Done
nullptr dereference.
Done

I thought we had a real privilege for this that we could check?  ConfigureSelf?

Also, I wouldn't expect this.  Admins should be allowed to do this for other users, right?

This api is used by the user while setting up the secret key on his/her mobile device after a createSecretKey call. This happens whenever a user tries to login for the first time after global MFA enablement. Admin calling this for other users means, we are enabling a use case where admin creating secret key for other users and sharing it out of band. Which is an insecure way of sharing.

I second what Abhilash has said.
It should be "ConfigureSelf" as the user should only setup/configure mfa by verifying the TOTP.

If you dislike the current state of privilege registry, you're free to go argue with DMTF that produced it.  At the moment, privilege registry states that admins have complete access.

I agree, an admin probably _shouldnt_ set up a secret key for a user, but that's not something we can argue in this patch..

yes right, any admin priv user should not setup a secret key for other user, that's why DMTF redfish came up generatedSecretKey registry which can be used to direct the same user to generate secret in session create flow..

I’m not going to continue to argue something on a forum that we have no influence on.  either:
1. get DMTF to change this, and mark this patch WIP until the next redfish release.
2. change this patchset for now to follow the privilege registry as it exists, then fix it once you’ve made your case to DMTF and a release is made.

Hi Ed.

Am getting that this API restricts to just "ConfigureSelf" even for the user with "priv-admin" role.

But I am unclear about the DMTF change you mention here. Can you please help here, so that we would atleast be able to decide to do the '2.' you have mentioned and take this commit forward.

> Hi Ed.
> 
> Am getting that this API restricts to just "ConfigureSelf" even for the user with "priv-admin" role.
> 
> But I am unclear about the DMTF change you mention here. Can you please help here, so that we would atleast be able to decide to do the '2.' you have mentioned and take this commit forward.

DMTF lists this API with a ConfigureUsers privilege, with some specific overrides for ConfigureSelf.

https://github.com/DMTF/Redfish-Publications/blob/ce5f0dc950120af8856b7aa10ae3c29fcae89c4f/registries/Redfish_1.5.0_PrivilegeRegistry.json#L6132
I opened an issue with the DTMF for this, see https://github.com/DMTF/Redfish/issues/6245#issuecomment-2407882528

That's good it's raised to them.  For the moment, actions use the POST permissions for the resource type in privilege registry as a rule.  Lets get that changed so we can get this merged, and once DMTF fixes the actions problem, we can regroup around "should an admin be allowed to set this", and whether we want to break the rules, or invent new rules for this case.
